Sentencas: Low thermal expansion Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-delta(BSCFM-0.1) material was prepared to improve the thermal compatibility between cathode and electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: The pure perovskite BSCFM-0.1 can be obtained by a combined citrate and EDTA complexing method.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: The results show that Mn was introduced to replace Co in B-site of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-delta(BSCF) to depress thermal expansion.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient of BSCFM-0.1 is 14.24x10(-6) K-1 at 600 degrees C, and 14.97x10(-6) K-1 at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: It is a smaller value comparing with BSCF for 15.62 x10(-6) K-1 at 600 degrees C and 16.76x10(-6) K-1 at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: The small difference of thermal expansion is helpful for cathode adhering to the ceria-base electrolyte.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: As to the single cell, the maximum power density is 110 mW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C, which is slightly higher than that of BSCF cathode (102 mW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C).
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: The results imply that the rate of lattice oxygen release has been slowed down to control the concentration of oxygen vacancies in the lattice by Mn partial substitution without reducing electrical properties.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material

Sentencas: The gradual increase of thermal expansion is beneficial to improve the thermal compatibility between cathode and electrolyte for SOFCs.
Titulo: Low Thermal Expansion of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.7Fe0.2Mn0.1O3-δ cathode Material
